set:
phongo
PHP driver for MongoDB




   Phongo is an experimental MongoDB driver for PHP, likely replacing the
    driver in the near future.


   Developed ontop of libmongoc
   and libbson, phongo is
   meant to be as basic as possible.


   Core MongoDB concepts are implemented, but everything else is left for
   other toolkits to come in and provide pretty and flexible bindings that
   make sense for their ecosystem.


   This makes the driver exceptionally fast, and really easy to work with and
   provide first class experience in your framework, library or application.


   The plan is to provide an example bindings, which you may chose to use -
   or ignore and make your own.




